blah_1977 wrote:
&gt;
&gt; OK, I see the Credential-related classes. Now in the CredentialStore
&gt; class there is a create() method. Can I use this method to
&gt; programmatically create a Credential during the course of crawling
&gt; when I discover forms whose submission needs an HTTP POST?
&gt;




Thats an interesting idea. 

A few points:

+ Before heritrix processes an URL, we check for preconditions such as 
DNS or robots.txt.  If absent, the URL is put aside until the 
preconditions are met.  The credentials system leverages this facility.  
An operator fills in credentials for servers that require login.  As 
heritrix encounters new hosts, along w/ DNS and robots.txt, it checks if 
it has credentials to offer for the newly-discovered host.  If it has, 
as a precondition, it first runs the supplied credentials.  Your 
suggestion, its likely, would be adding credentials -- and a 
precondition -- after we&#39;ve already begun crawling a particular host.  
The next URL from the host to which credentials have been 
programmatically attached will be put aside until the credentials have 
been run.  Adding a precondition after we&#39;ve already started in on a 
host should work -- after-all, robots.txt expires and we handle that 
gracefully -- but be warned there may be kinks/assumptions in here that 
need modification.
+ Be forewarned that it can be trying tracing the scheduling and the 
running of credentials since state spans more than a single-run down the 
processor-chain.  You have heritrix up in a debuggger?  And 6.2.3 
Credentials in the user manual, 
http://crawler.archive.org/articles/user_manual/config.html#submodules, 
shows how to enable credential logging.

Good luck and let us know how it goes for you.  Ask questions up here if 
you run into blocks or if you need changes made in heritrix core.

St.Ack


&gt;
&gt; --- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com 
&gt; &lt;mailto:archive-crawler%40yahoogroups.com&gt;, Michael Stack &lt;stack@...&gt; 
&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Heritrix only does HTTP POST when configured to supply login
&gt; &gt; credentials. See the 6.2.3. Credentials section on this page
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; http://crawler.archive.org/articles/user_manual/config.html#submodules, 
&gt; &lt;http://crawler.archive.org/articles/user_manual/config.html#submodules,&gt;
&gt; &gt; in particular 6.2.3.2. HTML Form POST or GET. Otherwise its HTTP
&gt; &gt; GET&#39;ing all day long.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; St.Ack
&gt; &gt;
&gt;
&gt;  


